## SDQ vs MAST

Software Psychologists and social scientists often have a need for comparing and matching different questionnaire items. For instance, comparing items in SDQ (Strengths and Difficulties Questionnaire) and MAST (Michigan Alcoholism Screening Test) requires a lot of manual work and time. But now, these daunting tasks can be easily performed with the Harmony software. SDQ vs MAST item comparison is made smoother and more efficient with this AI-powered tool. Harmony uses advanced natural language processing and AI models to harmonise questionnaire items across different instruments and even languages. In the case of SDQ vs MAST, simply upload your own PDF versions of the questionnaires or select from the existing database. The software calculates a percentage match between each item in SDQ and MAST, assisting in effective comparison and potential harmonisation. The tedious task of manual harmonisation and comparison of SDQ vs MAST items are significantly reduced with Harmony. Whether you're cross-referencing questions in different languages, or comparing questionnaires within one language, Harmony is a powerful tool for all psychologist and social scientist needs. Making comparisons both within and across studies has never been so straightforward and attainable, truly allowing for results consistency or differences analysis across varying social conditions.
